782
01:19:29,824 --> 01:19:34,412
<i>Following the distribution of the kits,
those of you who have p.m. Deadlines...</i>

783
01:19:34,662 --> 01:19:36,998
<i>... better dash to your phones.</i>

784
01:19:37,248 --> 01:19:41,877
<i>Now we'll have some questions
from the press, please.</i>

785
01:19:43,504 --> 01:19:46,298
<i>I'd like to know
whether your wives and children...</i>

786
01:19:46,548 --> 01:19:50,260
<i>... had anything to say about this.</i>

787
01:19:56,099 --> 01:19:59,227
<i>Mine think it's fine.</i>

788
01:20:09,487 --> 01:20:12,573
<i>They're all for it.</i>

789
01:20:22,541 --> 01:20:26,002
<i>I don't think any of us could go on
with something like this...</i>

790
01:20:26,253 --> 01:20:30,757
<i>... if we didn't have
pretty good backing at home.</i>

791
01:20:34,886 --> 01:20:37,680
<i>My wife's attitude towards this
has been the same...</i>

792
01:20:37,930 --> 01:20:40,683
<i>... as it's been all along through my flying.</i>

793
01:20:40,933 --> 01:20:43,978
<i>If it's what I want to do, she's behind it.</i>

794
01:20:44,228 --> 01:20:48,982
<i>And, by golly, my kids are, too.
100 percent.</i>

795
01:20:55,780 --> 01:20:57,782
I don't believe this.

796
01:20:58,032 --> 01:21:02,662
But look at them out there.
They're eating it up.

797
01:21:04,580 --> 01:21:07,458
<i>I was brought up believing
that you are placed on earth...</i>

798
01:21:07,708 --> 01:21:11,712
<i>... more or less with a 50-50 proposition.</i>

799
01:21:11,962 --> 01:21:14,715
<i>This is what I still believe.</i>

800
01:21:14,965 --> 01:21:18,260
<i>We're placed here with certain talents
and capabilities...</i>

801
01:21:18,510 --> 01:21:24,307
<i>... and it's up to each one of us
to use those talents as best we can.</i>

802
01:21:26,142 --> 01:21:29,145
<i>And if we use our talents properly...</i>

803
01:21:29,395 --> 01:21:33,232
<i>... I think there is a power
greater than us that will place...</i>

804
01:21:33,482 --> 01:21:37,236
<i>... the opportunities in our way.</i>

805
01:21:42,533 --> 01:21:45,285
<i>When I think of Orville and Wilbur Wright...</i>

806
01:21:45,535 --> 01:21:47,996
<i>... standing on a hill
at Kitty Hawk, North Carolina...</i>

807
01:21:48,246 --> 01:21:53,960
<i>... tossing a coin to see which one
would take the first airplane flight...</i>

808
01:21:54,002 --> 01:21:58,131
<i>... and then I think of us here today...</i>

809
01:22:01,592 --> 01:22:03,636
<i>... I thank God I live in a country...</i>

810
01:22:03,886 --> 01:22:08,724
<i>... where the best and finest in a man
can be brought out.</i>

811
01:22:20,402 --> 01:22:25,239
<i>I'd like to second some of the things
Mr. Glenn has said here.</i>

812
01:22:25,490 --> 01:22:30,494
<i>I think that we are all very,
very fortunate...</i>

813
01:22:30,745 --> 01:22:33,831
<i>... that we have been,
should we say, "blessed"...</i>

814
01:22:34,081 --> 01:22:36,917
<i>... with the talents for something like this.</i>

815
01:22:37,167 --> 01:22:41,380
<i>And I think that we would be most remiss
in our duty indeed...</i>

816
01:22:41,630 --> 01:22:45,509
<i>... if we did not volunteer
for something as important as this is...</i>

817
01:22:45,759 --> 01:22:47,260
<i>... for our country...</i>

818
01:22:47,510 --> 01:22:51,598
<i>... and to the world in general right now.</i>

819
01:22:54,767 --> 01:22:58,104
One of our Air Force boys.

820
01:22:58,187 --> 01:23:01,023
<i>Don't you agree, Deke?</i>

821
01:23:01,273 --> 01:23:03,609
<i>I absolutely agree with Gordo.</i>

822
01:23:03,859 --> 01:23:06,320
<i>But we're not saying anything new.</i>

823
01:23:06,570 --> 01:23:08,947
<i>We're just saying the same things...</i>

824
01:23:09,198 --> 01:23:15,036
<i>... that need to be said again
and again with fierce conviction.</i>

825
01:23:22,001 --> 01:23:26,214
Can you tell us if any of you
go to church regularly?

826
01:23:26,464 --> 01:23:29,175
<i>As far as church goes...</i>

827
01:23:29,425 --> 01:23:32,553
<i>... I attend regularly.</i>

828
01:23:35,305 --> 01:23:39,518
Which one of you will be
the first into space?

829
01:23:55,658 --> 01:23:59,370
<i>The best will be first.</i>

830
01:24:16,094 --> 01:24:19,055
Share it, brother.

831
01:24:19,555 --> 01:24:22,725
Fucking A, bubba.

832
01:24:24,185 --> 01:24:28,397
This is for America's "Life" magazine.

833
01:24:34,152 --> 01:24:39,199
These are the greatest pilots in America.

834
01:24:39,282 --> 01:24:41,242
How much do they make?

835
01:24:41,493 --> 01:24:43,411
$7,000-$8,000 a year?

836
01:24:43,661 --> 01:24:46,122
- Tops.
- At the most.

837
01:24:46,372 --> 01:24:49,959
With this one deal
I'm giving them $500,000...

838
01:24:50,209 --> 01:24:53,671
...split seven ways over three years.

839
01:24:53,921 --> 01:24:56,882
How does that sound?

840
01:24:57,132 --> 01:25:01,512
Now I want them all to meet my people
who will write their true stories.

841
01:25:01,762 --> 01:25:05,891
These stories will appear in "Life"
under their own by-lines.

842
01:25:06,141 --> 01:25:07,184
For example...

843
01:25:07,434 --> 01:25:10,437
..."by Betty Grissom"...

844
01:25:10,687 --> 01:25:12,230
...or, "by...

845
01:25:12,480 --> 01:25:16,025
...Virgil I. Grissom."

846
01:25:19,904 --> 01:25:20,780
What was that?

847
01:25:21,030 --> 01:25:21,906
Gus.

848
01:25:22,156 --> 01:25:25,826
Nobody calls me by that other name.

849
01:25:26,076 --> 01:25:27,703
Gus?

850
01:25:27,953 --> 01:25:31,873
An astronaut named Gus?

851
01:25:33,875 --> 01:25:35,127
What's your middle name?

852
01:25:35,377 --> 01:25:37,963
Ivan.

853
01:25:41,883 --> 01:25:44,427
Maybe...

854
01:25:45,053 --> 01:25:46,679
..."Gus" isn't so bad.

855
01:25:46,929 --> 01:25:50,182
Might be something there.

856
01:25:50,933 --> 01:25:54,812
All right, you can be Gus.

857
01:25:57,272 --> 01:26:00,692
I bet for all that money
they could call you Virgil.

858
01:26:00,942 --> 01:26:04,154
They sure could me.

859
01:26:09,117 --> 01:26:11,995
Well, what's with her?

860
01:26:12,245 --> 01:26:15,331
She seems snobby.

861
01:26:15,456 --> 01:26:17,124
I don't get it.

862
01:26:17,375 --> 01:26:21,921
I get it. She's "Mrs. Clean Marine".

863
01:26:33,640 --> 01:26:37,185
I'm going to the Cape tomorrow.

864
01:26:38,811 --> 01:26:43,024
I wish to heck it wasn't off-limits to wives.

865
01:26:43,399 --> 01:26:47,278
There's so much work to do, anyway.
More tests...

866
01:26:47,528 --> 01:26:48,571
...training...

867
01:26:48,821 --> 01:26:51,532
...studying.

868
01:26:57,829 --> 01:27:01,541
What about after?

869
01:27:02,667 --> 01:27:04,669
After hours I'll run a lot.

870
01:27:04,919 --> 01:27:07,422
I'm going to get up to five miles a day.

871
01:27:07,672 --> 01:27:10,675
There's a beautiful, long beach there.

872
01:27:10,925 --> 01:27:13,761
It's called Cocoa Beach.

873
01:27:14,011 --> 01:27:17,056
You can run forever.

874
01:27:17,681 --> 01:27:20,100
Scott Carpenter will run with me.

875
01:27:20,351 --> 01:27:22,436
He's a good guy.

876
01:27:22,686 --> 01:27:25,897
He's real philosophical.

877
01:27:28,191 --> 01:27:31,069
What about...?

878
