keep the Mickey Mouse to a minimum.

879
01:27:39,827 --> 01:27:42,913
They're good men.

880
01:27:43,164 --> 01:27:45,291
Good men.

881
01:27:45,541 --> 01:27:49,753
They'll give 100 percent
when the time comes.

882
01:27:54,216 --> 01:27:57,928
Guess they think I'm kind of a...

883
01:27:58,261 --> 01:28:01,431
...gung-ho type.

884
01:28:01,764 --> 01:28:04,767
"Eddie Attaboy."

885
01:28:05,184 --> 01:28:08,229
"Harry Hairshirt."

886
01:28:10,523 --> 01:28:13,400
What, you agree?

887
01:28:14,985 --> 01:28:16,070
You agree?

888
01:28:16,320 --> 01:28:19,156
My own wife.

889
01:28:19,448 --> 01:28:23,160
Do you think I'm a "Dudley Doright"?

890
01:28:25,829 --> 01:28:28,164
That's me, I guess.

891
01:28:28,415 --> 01:28:30,291
A lonely beacon of restraint...

892
01:28:30,542 --> 01:28:34,921
...and self-sacrifice
in a squall of car-crazies.

893
01:28:47,558 --> 01:28:52,771
It's important to America
to get a man up there first.

894
01:28:55,190 --> 01:28:59,444
I plan to be the first man
to ride the rocket.

895
01:31:50,229 --> 01:31:53,274
<i>What is the most important thing
in rocket travel?</i>

896
01:31:53,524 --> 01:31:56,986
<i>To me the most important thing...</i>

897
01:31:57,236 --> 01:31:59,321
<i>... is the blast-off.</i>

898
01:31:59,572 --> 01:32:03,575
<i>I always take a blast before I take off.</i>

899
01:32:04,243 --> 01:32:07,871
<i>Otherwise I wouldn't go near it.</i>

900
01:32:13,877 --> 01:32:17,046
He loves Ed Sullivan.

901
01:32:46,532 --> 01:32:50,745
Four down, three to go.

902
01:33:28,572 --> 01:33:32,659
I don't want anything to put this program
in a bad light.

903
01:33:32,909 --> 01:33:37,080
We have the opportunity of a lifetime
and I'm sorry, but I won't stand by...

904
01:33:37,330 --> 01:33:40,250
...and let other people compromise
the whole darned thing!

905
01:33:40,500 --> 01:33:44,337
You know and I know this could lead
to something very unfortunate.

906
01:33:44,587 --> 01:33:47,840
I'm talking about the playing around
that's going on.

907
01:33:48,090 --> 01:33:50,426
I'm talking about the young girls.

908
01:33:50,676 --> 01:33:52,219
I'm talking about the cookies.

909
01:33:52,470 --> 01:33:55,514
I'm talking about keeping our pants zipped
and our wicks dry.

910
01:33:55,764 --> 01:33:58,725
Mr. Glenn, you are way out of line.

911
01:33:58,976 --> 01:34:03,772
I advise you not to try to foist your
moral views on anyone else in this group.

912
01:34:04,022 --> 01:34:06,149
Each man here has volunteered to do a job.

913
01:34:06,399 --> 01:34:09,194
Each man is devoting long hours
of training...

914
01:34:09,444 --> 01:34:12,530
...and doing many things above
and beyond the call of duty...

915
01:34:12,780 --> 01:34:14,699
...such as morale tours of factories...

916
01:34:14,949 --> 01:34:16,867
Such as bringing girls up to your room?

917
01:34:17,118 --> 01:34:19,495
And forgoing any orderly family life.

918
01:34:19,745 --> 01:34:22,539
Mr. Glenn, as long
as a man uses good sense...

919
01:34:22,790 --> 01:34:26,835
...what he does with his wick
is his own business!

920
01:34:27,085 --> 01:34:29,671
I'm from "Life" magazine.
I'm not with these people.

921
01:34:29,921 --> 01:34:34,676
You can't go in.
They're discussing scientific problems.

922
01:34:37,512 --> 01:34:40,556
John's right. Whether we like it or not
we're public figures.

923
01:34:40,807 --> 01:34:43,351
Whether we deserve it or not,
people look up to us.

924
01:34:43,601 --> 01:34:45,770
We have a tremendous responsibility.

925
01:34:46,020 --> 01:34:50,733
You can't tell a pilot what to do
when he's not flying.

926
01:34:54,278 --> 01:34:56,196
Wait a minute. You got it all wrong.

927
01:34:56,446 --> 01:34:58,490
The issue here ain't pussy.

928
01:34:58,740 --> 01:35:00,492
The issue here is monkey.

929
01:35:00,742 --> 01:35:05,413
Us. We are the monkey.

930
01:35:07,081 --> 01:35:09,751
What Gus is saying is
that we're missing the point.

931
01:35:10,001 --> 01:35:14,213
Gus is saying that we all heard rumors
they want to send a monkey up first.

932
01:35:14,463 --> 01:35:17,716
None of us wants them to send
a monkey up to do a man's work.

933
01:35:17,967 --> 01:35:19,551
What Gus is saying is that...

934
01:35:19,802 --> 01:35:23,680
...what they're trying to do to us
is send a man up to do a monkey's work.

935
01:35:23,931 --> 01:35:26,892
Us. A bunch of
college-trained chimpanzees.

936
01:35:27,142 --> 01:35:30,604
What Gus is saying is that
we've got to change things around here.

937
01:35:30,854 --> 01:35:33,314
He's saying that we are pilots.

938
01:35:33,565 --> 01:35:36,734
We know more about what we need
to fly than anybody else.

939
01:35:36,985 --> 01:35:39,904
So what we have to do
is alter the experiment.

940
01:35:40,154 --> 01:35:43,824
It comes down to who is going
to control this thing from here on.

941
01:35:44,075 --> 01:35:49,455
What Gus is saying here is
that we've got to stick together on this.

942
01:36:55,767 --> 01:36:58,186
These tests were designed...

943
01:36:58,436 --> 01:37:01,356
...to decondition, to desensitize...

944
01:37:01,606 --> 01:37:04,609
...to adapt out fears.

945
01:37:04,859 --> 01:37:09,196
Since we have developed
a fully automated vehicle...

946
01:37:09,447 --> 01:37:11,615
...all we seek from the occupants...

947
01:37:11,866 --> 01:37:14,201
...of the capsule is data.

948
01:37:14,451 --> 01:37:16,954
The so-called astronaut...

949
01:37:17,204 --> 01:37:22,000
...would merely be a redundant component.

950
01:37:23,543 --> 01:37:24,669
And here you can see...

951
01:37:24,919 --> 01:37:28,673
...these chimps are capable of many
of the same tasks as men.

952
01:37:28,923 --> 01:37:32,677
And they are much more cooperative.

953
01:37:35,304 --> 01:37:38,974
<i>They are being put through every phase
of the astronaut training.</i>

954
01:37:39,225 --> 01:37:42,895
<i>As far as we are concerned,
the question still remains:</i>

955
01:37:43,145 --> 01:37:45,147
<i>Which one will be first?</i>

956
01:37:45,397 --> 01:37:46,815
<i>The man or...</i>

957
01:37:47,065 --> 01:37:49,067
<i>... the monkey?</i>

958
01:37:49,317 --> 01:37:52,070
<i>We shall see.</i>

959
01:38:22,015 --> 01:38:25,268
Take it easy with that.

960
01:38:32,149 --> 01:38:35,069
- Where are you putting the window?
- Window?

961
01:38:35,319 --> 01:38:36,320
There is no window.

962
01:38:36,570 --> 01:38:38,864
No window?

963
01:38:39,114 --> 01:38:41,867
What about the hatch?

964
01:38:42,117 --> 01:38:45,162
We need a hatch with explosive bolts,
that we can open ourselves.

965
01:38:45,412 --> 01:38:47,747
There's something you don't understand.

966
01:38:47,998 --> 01:38:50,333
This is the final form of the capsule.

967
01:38:50,583 --> 01:38:51,668
No hatch.

968
01:38:51,918 --> 01:38:54,796
What would happen
if the automatic controls went out?

969
01:38:55,046 --> 01:38:58,216
With backups, checks,
this would not happen.

970
01:38:58,466 --> 01:39:00,801
I said, what would happen if it did?

971
01:39:01,052 --> 01:39:02,595
The pilot would have to fly it back.

972
01:39:02,845 --> 01:39:05,639
This is the way it is.

973
01:39:05,889 --> 01:39:08,976
I wonder how the press will feel about this.

974
01:39:09,226 --> 01:39:13,647
The press? What does the press
have to say about this?

975
01:39:13,897 --> 01:39:17,901
Do you boys know
what makes this bird go up?

976
01:39:18,151 --> 01:39:20,445
Funding makes this bird go up.

977
01:39:20,695 --> 01:39:23,489
That's right. No bucks...

978
01:39:23,740 --> 01:39:25,158
...no Buck Rogers.

979
01:39:25,408 --> 01:39:29,495
And the press over there...

980
01:39:35,626 --> 01:39:37,503
They all want to see Buck Rogers.

981
01:39:37,753 --> 01:39:39,630
And that's us.

982
01:39:39,880 --> 01:39:41,214
Buck Rogers.

983
01:39:41,465 --> 01:39:44,509
You see, those fellows over there
have been making us out...

984
01:39:44,759 --> 01:39:48,805
...as the seven finest and bravest pilots
in all America.

985
01:39:49,055 --> 01:39:52,600
If the story would come out in the press...

986
01:39:52,850 --> 01:39:55,144
...that we are not allowed to fly as pilots...

987
01:39:55,394 --> 01:39:58,439
We want a window.

988
01:40:00,232 --> 01:40:02,192
There could maybe be...

989
01:40:02,443 --> 01:40:07,114
...in future capsules a window...

990
01:40:07,155 --> 01:40:08,365
...here.

991
01:40:08,615 --> 01:40:11,326
No, that's where the hatch
with explosive bolts goes.

992
01:40:11,576 --> 01:40:15,163
The hatch with the explosive...

993
01:40:17,123 --> 01:40:20,460
There could be a hatch
with explosive bolts on the capsule.

994
01:40:20,710 --> 01:40:23,379
That is a spacecraft, sir.

995
01:40:23,629 --> 01:40:27,508
We do not refer to it as a "capsule".

996
01:40:28,300 --> 01:40:31,178
Spacecraft.

997
01:40:32,471 --> 01:40:35,224
A hatch with explosive bolts on the...

998
01:40:35,474 --> 01:40:38,351
...spacecraft.

999
01:40:39,769 --> 01:40:43,314
And there will be pitch and yaw thrusters
to enable the occupant...

1000
01:40:43,565 --> 01:40:46,192
The pilot.

1001
01:40:46,734 --> 01:40:49,737
Astronaut-pilot?

1002
01:40:51,572 --> 01:40:53,741
The astronaut...

1003
01:40:53,991 --> 01:40:56,702
...pilot...

1004
01:40:56,952 --> 01:40:58,787
...to have some...

1005
01:40:59,038 --> 01:41:01,832
...to have...

1006
01:41:03,625 --> 01:41:06,378
...control...

1007
01:41:07,212 --> 01:41:10,757
...of the re-entry procedures.

1008
01:41:14,177 --> 01:41:15,553
We appreciate it.

1009
01:41:15,803 --> 01:41:21,601
You wouldn't mind if we had the press
take a few photos of us, would you?

1010
01:41:53,672 --> 01:41:59,386
Which one of you is going to be
the first one to be launched into space?

1011
01:42:34,628 --> 01:42:36,546
Here he is.

1012
01:42:36,796 --> 01:42:40,216
Captain Ham.

1013
01:42:40,675 --> 01:42:44,887
Grinning like a possum
eating a sweet potato.

1014
01:42:46,013 --> 01:42:50,768
Does he look like the kind of guy
who'd put doo-doo in the capsule?

1015
01:42:51,018 --> 01:42:53,687
Ham in a can.

1016
01:42:54,563 --> 01:42:57,858
America's first astronaut. Look at him!

1017
01:42:58,108 --> 01:43:04,531
You take a monkey like this,
you can make him into a great astronaut.